TopicTitle: Crash on loadscreen after switching from Kethane to Kerbanite

Articles.Content:
So, I removed the Kethane folder from gamedata and added most of the stuff from the USI Catalogue (Kerbanite & Co), also installed ORS.

Then I installed the EPL to Kerbanite Conversion.

When loading the game, I now get a filenotfound derivative near the end of the loadingscreen.

Here the log:

https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/44766482/KSP%20Report/output_log.txt

Here the filetree of gamedata:

https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/44766482/KSP%20Report/tree.txt

My guess is that I'm missing some required mod or something is outdated. But I personally can't identify what from looking at the log and the mods I added.

Oh yeah, Windows 64Bit (7) using 32Bit KSP.

Edit:

Edited December 16, 2014 by Berserker66

USI mods size (incl. Karbonite) is greater than Kethane size.

Check your RAM amount being used. If needed - try ATM (http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/59005-0-23-5-Release-3-1-Active-Texture-Management-Save-RAM-without-reduction-packs!)
Switched to OpenGL and that did the trick for me.
